---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility"
  description="Accessibility statement for the Ocean Recoveries Lab website."
>
  <section class="section bg-surface">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-8">Accessibility Statement</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p class="lead">
          The Ocean Recoveries Lab is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for all users,
          including those with disabilities.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          We strive to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards. Our website is designed to be:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Navigable using keyboard alone</li>
          <li>Compatible with screen readers</li>
          <li>Readable with sufficient color contrast</li>
          <li>Responsive across different devices and screen sizes</li>
          <li>Respectful of user preferences for reduced motion</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Skip navigation links for keyboard users</li>
          <li>Alt text for images</li>
          <li>Semantic HTML structure</li>
          <li>ARIA labels where appropriate</li>
          <li>Focus indicators for interactive elements</li>
          <li>Dark mode support following system preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
        <p>
          While we work to ensure accessibility, some content may have limitations:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Some older PDF documents may not be fully accessible</li>
          <li>Third-party content (embedded maps, external links) may have varying accessibility</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Feedback</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of this website. If you encounter
          barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:astier@ucsb.edu">astier@ucsb.edu</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>UC Santa Barbara Resources</h2>
        <p>
          For more information about accessibility at UC Santa Barbara, visit the
          <a href="https://www.accessibility.ucsb.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            UCSB Accessibility website
          </a>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-8">
          Last updated: December 2024
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    @apply text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4;
  }

  .prose p {
    @apply text-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed;
  }

  .prose ul {
    @apply list-disc list-inside text-muted mb-4 space-y-1;
  }

  .prose a {
    @apply text-accent hover:underline;
  }
</style>
